Rating: 4
Had trouble finding chipotle en adobo in my local stores a year ago so I developed my own small quantity, quick version. Take one dried chipotle chili, remove seeds, chop, add 1/2 c. hot water, 1/2 tbl ketchup, 1 clove chopped garlic, pinch salt, and 1/2 tbl apple cider, let sit on the counter for 1/2-1 hour. Can blend if desired. I put desired quantity in a recipe and then serve the rest on the side for those who like a bigger zip. Try it in this great recipe!

