Rating: 3
So quick and easy. I used 2 cans of black beans and added carrots and celery. Since I had some fresh salsa that was on the verge, I used 1 cup of that instead of the second can of tomatoes. With only 1 1/2 cup of broth, it thickened nicely without the blender. The chipoltes added great flavor and lots of heat. Topped with cilantro and non-fat yogurt for a lower calorie version. Looking forward to the leftovers tonight.

Rating: 3
Serious numminess! But don't put it in the blender. We enjoyed the crunchiness of the peppers and beans. The texture of the veggies adds to the dish. Pleasantly spicy, without being too hot. We tried the sourcream on the side. Did not like how the cream made the dish bland. However, the Jack cheese was a great addition. Cut the dish in half for my husband and me, and we had great leftovers. With cutting the dish in half (and the amount of liquid from the tomatoes) I did not need to add the broth. Stick with the yellow peppers; they add a hint of sweetness that would not be found in green or red peppers. Going to add this to my beef/kidney bean chili recipe. Wonderful!

