This was the best tasting chili I ever made (and I make chili often). I assume the chipolte made the big difference. However, I cringed at using the food processor to "thicken" the mix and therefore used only half the tomatoes and veg broth called for. The result: thick, lush and delicious. Also, in Europe they don't have "roasted garlic tomatoes" so I used normal pureed tomatoes and added my own garlic. (PS I also couldn't get canned black beans here and so made them from scratch.) This was even better the next day. My chief food critic complained when he found it had all been eaten.

