Rating: 4
This is very good, and easy to prepare. It's done in about an hour, including chopping the vegetables. Six tablespoons of olive oil is quite a lot of oil. I used four, and it was still a little much. I found the canned chipotle chilis in abodo sauce in the supermarket. I deseeded them to reduce the spiciness, and actually used about 5 tablespoons. They weren't very spicy, but added a wonderful flavor. I topped the chili with grated pizza cheese (combination of chedder and mozzaralla), and served it with hot sourdough bread wedges. I will definitely make this again.

