Rating: 4
First I questioned the use of yellow peppers which was to be dumped in with the black beans and tomatoes and stewed for half an hour - WHY YELLOW PEPPERS? What's wrong with red or green bell peppers? They all end up the same color anyway. Then I couldn't find chipotle peppers - what do you expect - me living in Kuala Lumpur. So I used dried Sechuan peppers instead plus a small spoon of Trinidadian Chatak's Pepper sauce. Darn it! I couldn't find garlic - so in went Lee Kum Kee's Black bean and Garlic. Then came the tasting bit - no spoonfull at a time for this cook. I took just a small bowl and sat down to watch TV - then another smallish bowl. It was then that I realised that I was supposed to put this wonderful veggie-chili in a blender - NO WAY! I microwaved two imported Idaho potatoes to perfection - crushed and split them and filled them generously overflowing in a deep dish and topped it off with a good dollop of sour cream. Sorry next time I'll make spread as per the recipe - but please don't call this a salad - and mention colors that aren't there. Suzie Speedhump

